review_body: Excellent reader, interface is very buttery smooth

Agonisingly slow to load large files. And there is no option for highlighting text. Go for it only if you need a basic viewer that can open small pdf files.  PS : It is not an app rather an add on. You won't have an icon to launch it. It will only show up if you try to open a pdf file.

Simple and gets the work done. All basic features are there and it there is no icon in app drawer so it doesn't come in your way. 4mb in size and no background processes. In short,  it's exactly what I wanted. If you're a heavy pdf reader,  you're on the wrong page. But, it's more then enough for ca...Full ReviewSimple and gets the work done. All basic features are there and it there is no icon in app drawer so it doesn't come in your way. 4mb in size and no background processes. In short,  it's exactly what I wanted. If you're a heavy pdf reader,  you're on the wrong page. But, it's more then enough for casual users like me.

Better than Google Drive Viewer because Google Drive Viewer can intercept downloads which is frustrating. I've been looking for a PDF viewer that supports links, not just hyperlinks but links to go to another page in the PDF, and table of contents. The other PDF viewers have these 2 features are blo...Full ReviewBetter than Google Drive Viewer because Google Drive Viewer can intercept downloads which is frustrating. I've been looking for a PDF viewer that supports links, not just hyperlinks but links to go to another page in the PDF, and table of contents. The other PDF viewers have these 2 features are bloated with many other features I don't need. I think a plain PDF viewer added with these 2 features is definitely worth 5 stars anyday.
